The paper deals with classification problems in which the label space has structure, and proposes a new model that extends a previous model combining a conditional random field (CRF) with a deep neural network (DNN). The paper focuses on visual object classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a deep neural network also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with probabilistic relations between labels, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of a CRF suggests that it could belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with inference methods, which suggests that it could belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
